data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Action<...>` signature replaces `Expression<Func<...>>`, so manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` code won't compile anymore — but the fix is a dramatic simplification.

---

### 2. Complex type column naming — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF will auto-append a number (e.g., `Street1`). Pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path in column names.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City` but is now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Pin with `HasColumnName()` to keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, a =>
        {
            a.Property(x => x.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

Without these fixes, EF will generate a migration that **renames your columns**, which can break existing data.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL for safe logging
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
}
```

Update all method signatures on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
